NF regulatory sequences in Paenibacillus riograndensis SBR5<sup>T</sup> genome. We identified GlnR-binding sites flanking \xcf\x83<sup>A</sup> -binding sites upstream from BNF-related genes. GlnR binding to these sites was demonstrated by surface plasmon resonance spectroscopy. GlnR-DNA affinity is greatly enhanced when GlnR is in complex with feedback-inhibited (glutamine-occupied) glutamine synthetase (GS). GlnR-GS complex formation is also modulated by ATP and AMP. Thereby, gene repression exerted by the GlnR-GS complex is coupled with nitrogen (glutamine levels) and energetic status (ATP and AMP). Finally, we propose a DNA-looping model based on multiple operator sites that represents a strong and strict regulation for these genes.</AbstractText>\n                <CopyrightInformation>\xc2\xa9 2017 Federation of European Biochemical Societies.</CopyrightInformation>\n            </Abstract>\n            <AuthorList CompleteYN="Y">\n                <Author ValidYN="Y">\n                    <LastName>Fernandes</LastName>\n                    <ForeName>Gabriela de C</ForeName>\n                    <Initials>GC</Initials>\n                    <AffiliationInfo>\n                        <Affiliation>Departamento de Gen\xc3\xa9tica, Instituto de Bioci\xc3\xaancias, Universidade Federal do Rio Grande do Sul, Porto Alegre, RS, Brazil.</Affiliation>\n                    </AffiliationInfo>\n                    <AffiliationInfo>\n                        <Affiliation>Interfaculty Institute for Microbiology and Infection Medicine, University of Tuebingen, Germany.</Affiliation>\n                    </AffiliationInfo>\n                </Author>\n                <Author ValidYN="Y">\n                    <LastName>Hauf</LastName>\n                    <ForeName>Ksenia</ForeName>\n                    <Initials>K</Initials>\n                    <AffiliationInfo>\n                        <Affiliation>Interfaculty Institute for Microbiology and Infection Medicine, University of Tuebi